attributes.description: Overview dashboard for ActiveMQ managed by AmazonMQ.

params.markdown:
# ActiveMQ

This dashboard offers insights into key details related to ActiveMQ in AmazonMQ including

- Broker CPU and disk utilization
- Broker network and EBS volume utilization
- Enqueue, dequeue, producer, consumer metrics related to queues
- Enqueue, dequeue, producer, consumer metrics related to topics

The established connection count is the total number of connections, active and inactive, that have been established on the broker.

The current connection count is the current number of active connections on the current broker.

Consumer count is the number of messages consumers subscribed to destinations on the current broker.

Producer count is the number of message producers active on destinations on the current broker.
The number of messages stored on the broker.
NetworkIn is the volume of incoming traffic for the broker. NetworkOut is the volume of outgoing traffic for the broker.

Read operations volume is the number of read operations performed on the Amazon EBS volume.

Write operations volume is the number of write operations performed on the Amazon EBS volume.
